{
  "stem": "19111.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 396.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so they were still run by the Zionist organizations.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They brought that horrible news of what was going on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And even though we-- we heard the news with-- and we felt that the Russian might-- the Soviet Union-- with all its tanks and all that are very strong.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we felt sort of, in a way, secure.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The mere fact that the Germans occupied the Western part of Poland and-- and the Russians came in on the eastern side of-- we felt that perhaps we are in a safe zone.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And even if we didn't feel safe and wanted to get out of there, it-- it wasn't easy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, Vilna-- Vilna had between 60,000 or 70,000 Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And how many were able to get out?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even if they tried their hardest way was they had to go through the Soviet Union and all the-- it was practically impossible.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So with these new arrivals from Poland, then, with the Communist regime, was there any change in the relationship between the Jews of Vilna and the non-Jews, or the Gentiles, of Vilna at that time?",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that time, not really.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were a lot of Jewish people who were Communists themselves, you know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, the more Jewish people were involved in-- in the government jobs at that time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I would imagine Poles may have resented that, you know, to-- in a way.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the Communist Party had Poles and Jews, everybody in it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a matter of, I guess on the Polish part, to suppress their feelings at the time, since they were under the occupation of the Russians.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was really something.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Russians came into our town in-- can't remember exactly the date.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was 1939.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
